In the case of the arrest of Yuichi Okubo (42) and Naoki Yamamoto (43), both doctors, on suspicion of commissioned murder for administering drugs to a female patient with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), an incurable disease, it was found on the 25th that a "barbiturate-based" sedative was detected in the woman's body.
The prefectural police believe that he was given a sedative through a "gastric wax" in which nutrients are placed in the stomach through a tube.
According to medical officials, barbiturates-based drugs are used to treat epilepsy and other diseases and are not commercially available.
If administered in large doses, it may suppress breathing and lead to death, and is used by assisted suicide groups in Europe and the United States.
Oita River's body turned out to be an inn business man The death toll due to the Kyushu torrential rain has risen to 73|Shizuoka Shimbun ATS
Oita Prefecture announced on the 25th that the identity of the body found on the 23rd in the Oita River in Yufu City, the same prefecture was confirmed as Kenta Watanabe (28) = Yufuin Town, Yufuin Town = who was missing due to heavy rain.
The total number of deaths in the prefecture due to heavy rain was 4, and the death toll in Kyushu was 73.
The prefectural government also revealed on the 25th that the body of one person, of unknown gender and age, was found in a bamboo bush in Shonaihara, Shonai Town, the same city.
The body is believed to be one of Watanabe's parents, whose whereabouts are unknown, and efforts are being made to confirm their identity and determine the cause of death.
From midnight on the 7th to the 8th, Mr. Watanabe and his car were swept away by the swollen river.
Watanabe's body was found near the opposite shore where his grandmother, 81-year-old Tomi, was found.
Disney announces indefinite postponement of "Mulan" "Avatar" "Star Wars" also postponed (cinemacafe.net) --Yahoo! News
A few days ago, in the United States, where there was no sign of the new coronavirus infection coming under control, Warner Bros. decided to postpone the release of Christopher Nolan's "Tenet" for the third time (indefinitely).
[Photo] "Avatar" and "Star Wars" are also postponed ...
On the 23rd (local time), Disney also announced the indefinite postponement of "Mulan" following Warner.
The film was originally scheduled for a nationwide release on March 27, but was later rescheduled to July 24 and August 21.
A Disney spokesperson said, "With such a global health crisis in recent months, it is difficult to determine how the film will be released, so we would like to pause the release of 'Mulan' and think about how to effectively reach audiences around the world."
In addition to "Mulan," Disney has also postponed its release.
"Avatar," which has already been more than 10 years since its predecessor, is one of them.
Director James Cameron posted a letter on Twitter.
"Everything was fine until the outbreak of the new coronavirus, and it was scheduled to be released in December 2021," he said, before explaining that there was a significant delay in the production of the film, and that he was sad, saying, "I'm the one who is more disappointed than anyone else about this delay."
The second Avatar film is expected to be released in December 2022, one year away, the third in 2024, the fourth in 2026, and the fifth in 2028.
The new Star Wars trilogy has also been pushed back by a year, with the first film in December 2023, the second in 2025, and the third in 2027.
Karamon illuminated by colorful fireworks and lights launched at a nationwide event = Ichijoya Asakura ruins in Fukui City, Fukui Prefecture on the night of July 24
On the night of July 24, less than a year before the opening of the Tokyo Olympics, which were postponed due to the spread of the new coronavirus, the Junior Chamber of Japan (JC) held a nationwide fireworks event to brighten up society as much as possible.
Unfortunately, the weather in Fukui Prefecture was rainy and unfortunate, but the launch was carried out as scheduled at nine locations, coloring the summer night sky.
In the hope that it would be a signal to overcome the sense of stagnation caused by the spread of infection and to reinvent Japan, JC called on each block council nationwide to realize it.
It started at 8 p.m. at 117 locations in 46 prefectures.
At the ruins of the Asakura clan in Fukui City, a total of 53 rounds of No. 2~4 balls were launched for about two minutes while the surrounding mountains were covered with haze.
The light of the fireworks made the Karamon gate stand out in the dark night, creating a fantastic atmosphere.
In the prefecture, it was also held on the Matsubara coast in Tsuruga City and along the Mana River in Ono City.
In order to prevent infection, the launch site was not announced in advance in order to avoid a large number of onlookers.
